    CLI404Page
    This class is displayed to the client when the server can't be reached.
    CLI404Page.Default
     
    CLIChooseQuestPage
    This class represents the CLI page where the player can choose its private quest before the start of the match Page creation and management is done through the State design pattern, as previous pages When calling the print method, the page will be displayed with the two quests passed as arguments InvalidInput state is used to display an error message when the player inputs an invalid choice
    CLIChooseQuestPage.Default
    This class represents the default state of the page, where the player can choose its private quest Two quests are displayed on the screen, with their points and description The player can choose between the two of them by typing 1 or 2 Quest must be passed as an argument to the print method
    CLIChooseQuestPage.InvalidInput
     
    CLIChooseQuestPage.WaitingState
    This class is used to display a waiting message after the player has chosen its quest and is waiting for other players to do the same.
